704657f-a.text:
Goodwin Place, south side, between Greene Ave., and Grove Street. The building in the center, housed the Bauman Storage Co.; now occupied by H.C. Bohack & Ce., (1929). The upper story was destroyed by fire in 1923.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704656f-a.text:
20 Goodwin Place, south side, east of Greene Ave., showing a building belonging to A.E. Mills in 1869. (It was still standing in 1929.)

1923.
